<p><b>The First Council of Nicea</b> was convened in <a href="/wiki/Nicaea_(city)" title="Nicaea (city)" class="mw-redirect">Nicaea</a> in <a href="/wiki/Bithynia" title="Bithynia">Bithynia</a> (present-day <a href="/wiki/%C4%B0znik" title="İznik">İznik</a> in <a href="/wiki/Turkey" title="Turkey">Turkey</a>) by the <a href="/wiki/Roman_Emperors" title="Roman Emperors" class="mw-redirect">Roman Emperor</a> <a href="/wiki/Constantine_I" title="Constantine I">Constantine I</a> in 325 CE. The Council was historically significant as the first effort to attain <a href="/wiki/Consensus_decision-making" title="Consensus decision-making">consensus</a> in the church through an <a href="/wiki/Legislature" title="Legislature">assembly</a> representing all of <a href="/wiki/Christendom" title="Christendom">Christendom</a>. <sup id="cite_ref-dictionary_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-dictionary-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
